To determine the variable with greatest influence for the model prediction in each grid cell, we performed limiting factor analysis. For any given point, the limiting factor is the variable with a value change at that point that results in the greatest change in the predicted probability of species occurrence (
 Elith, Kearney & Phillips, 2010; 
 Elith et al., 2011). We focused on the limiting climatic factors affecting the contraction and expansion of climate suitability. The algorithm for the limiting factor analysis was programmed into MaxEnt, and the ‘density.tools.LimitingFactor’ command was used.
